Rating: 4
This soup gets 4 forks for the aroma alone. It was positively heavenly! I didn't have any leeks on hand, so I subbed in more onion, probably about half the amount to account for the strength. I also had some leftover red wine that I wanted to use up (a typical Rhone blend) so I used that for the wine and the water. It was understandably potent, but the flavor was wonderful. All those delicious veggies with the potent flavor of the wine--I felt like I was making an offering to Bacchus! I'm a fan of chunky soups, but I must admit that this soup is best when fully pureed.

