Rating: 4
This soup was amazing - my husband was mmmmming throughout dinner. This recipe made a big enough batch that we enjoyed it for lunches & froze some as well. I added nutmeg & cinnamon when cooking & then sprinkled some apple pie spice on each bowl for a little extra & presentation. Also - I am lactose intolerant so I put in some tuffuti cream cheese instead of sour cream which was good but not necessary. There's definitely some prep work invovled with all the peeling but it's not overwhelming. I highly recommend an immersion blender! Makes the pureeing SO much easier! I would definitely make this again! Especially around the holidays. It was delicious!

Rating: 4
I've been making this soup every year for Thanksgiving since the recipe first appeared in Gourmet in November 1992. It is a huge hit, and it is an unconditionally great recipe. If you follow it as it is written, and that means including all the ingredients, you will get a delicious soup. Don't add any of the spices that people suggest--you will be creating a whole different recipe that isn't true to the intent of this one.

